flowPara.flowSpan: N strmlnd, head points dwn, not fwd, sml platelike usually oval gls, 2 or 3T, mid short or abs. D minute or no hndW, 2T. All wtrs, but esp slw to mod rich, weedy. N excellent darting (3-6") swimmer (vert undulations, legs trailing), often in the drift, multiple broods, so good searching pat. To emerge, N buoy w internal gas and swim quickly to surface, D slowly humps up out of floating shuck, steps free, floats while unfurling wings, flitters off. Pref overcast days. Spinner falls often important.

flowRoot.flowPara: N lng antennae, dbl, heart-shaped gils, 3 hairy, interlocking T, still wtrs - Callibaetis ferrugineus (8-10 spr, 5-6mm fall) dors-dkOG, but var, vent-C/O, W-G/BBk w Wt veins. N usu color of surroundings. Mult practice runs up and dwn, but then D flit off quickly. S dors-dkB, vent-plG, W-clr w G or B splotches. Early season S esp important. O of highly ripened eggs can be days after mating. F dip abdo.
N single gls, 2 or 3 uneq fringed T, D tiny hind wngs - N B or lt/dkO, rounded platelike gls. F crawl down or dive to lay eggs on substrate.
2T - Baetis bicaudatus, Labiobaetis propinquus (4-5mm) plO, W-plG. N B w pl&dk mrks. S thx-B, F abdo-tan/B w O cast, M abdo-ltB, B nr tail.

3T - B. tricaudatus (4-9mm) O/dkB, W-lt/medG, L-C. N OB, lt dorsal stripe, gl veinlets vis, S thx-dkRB, F abdo-dkO/RB, M abdo-GB, W-clr w tan discolor. Diphetor hageni (7-5mm) ltO/dkB, W-G/dkG, L-C. N ltOB. S F B/tanB, M thx-dkB, abdo-ltC but B nr T. E spr wtr wrms to 40ºF, fall cools low 40s.

flowPara.flowSpan: - in weeds, E by climbing to tops, then swimming up, otherwise, gas buoy to film, X there. FS important.

flowSpan.flowSpan: B. punctiventris (4-5mm) plO/Ch, W-pl/medG. N plO/Ch. S F thx-dkGr/dkOB, abdo-brGr/dkOB. B. futile, Acentrella turbida

flowPara.flowSpan: dkB, W-lt/medG, N plO. FS like punctiventris.

flowRoot.flowPara: Family N-nymphs, D-duns, A-adults, S-spinner, Stage Omitted-dun, F-female, M-male, W-wings, L-legs, T-tails, Part Omitted-bdy, B-brn, O-Olv, G-gry, Gn-grn, Ch-chartruse, Y-yel, C-crm, R-red, Bk-blk, Wt-white, br-bright, lt-light, pl-pale, dk-drk, /-ranges to. S wngs clear (hyaline) if omitted.

flowPara.flowSpan: N strmlnd, slightly flattened, platelike gls, posterolateral spines segs 8, 9 only, 3 hairy, interlocking T. D rel lrg hndW, 2T. Excellent, darting swimmers (vert undulations, legs trailing), migrate to slow, almost still wtr, swim to bank (fish with short, darting strips || to bank), crawl out to emerge, so not avail to trout, sometimes dense spinner fall in orig wtr. E spr wtr wrms to low 60s.
N flattened conf, head as wide as body, eyes on top of head, gls platelike, on segs 1-7, 3T, except

D 5 segs on hind tarsi, hind wng 1/3 as large as fore, prob plain wngs, 2T. The fastest wtr specs have the largest gls, esp seg 1, which can extend under the abdomen. Gls on slow wtr genera are small. Some migrate to slower wtr. All eclose while still underwater, break surface as duns and fly off rel quickly. In the fastest wtr, eclosion is at the bottom, in slower near the film. Spinners can be important. Migrating genera spin over orig fast wtr.

flowRoot.flowPara: N side-protruding mouth parts, med veined gls, 3T - Cinygmula ramaleyi (7-8mm) RB/dkOB, W-dkG, T-G. N lt/dkRB. E wtr wrms hi 40s. C. reticulata (8mm) tanB/orng, W-Y, T-C. N ltRB, rdsh gls.

N 2 bdy len T, lrg lat held gls - Epeorus - N thx-OB, abdo-lt/drkChocB. Adults widely sep tls, F make mult brief touch downs w 6-10' rises before fallling spent. E. alberti, deceptivus (9-11mm) G/ltC, F pnksh cast, W-ltG, T-C/tan. S M C/GC, F pinkR, W-clr w B veins. E. longimanus (10-14mm) ltG w drkr tergites, W-G/dk slate, T-G w brn mrks. E in spr runoff, wtr wrms to high 40s(?). S plY/RB, W-clr w dkB veins.

N sm gry to wht gls, 3 bdy len T - Heptagenia complex - N lt/dkOB w poss G cast, paler mrks, T-ltG w bnds. F make mult brief touch downs before fallling spent. Heptagenia elegantula (9-10mm) CY/orng, W-lt/tanG, L&T-C, most restricted range in cplx. E wtr wrms to 50ºF. S thx-RC, abdo-ltG, W-clr w Bk veins. H. solitaria (10-12mm) Ytan belly, tan tergs, W-ltG w Y cast, T-tanG. S tan w Y bnds. Ecdyonurus criddlei (8mm)- RB w "V" mrks, W-G, T-B. S thx-dkB, abdo-ltB w mks, W-clr w B veins E. simplicioides (10-11mm) ltC, W-ltG/tanG, T-tanG. S thx-YC, abdo-plC/Wt, W-clr w tan hue & pl veins.

N gls lrg gry to dk gry, 3T, bdy len spekld brn - Rhithrogena - N dkRB. R. hageni, morrisoni (9-10, 8-9mm) purplshBk, W- mot B, folded back,T-dkGB. Early seas morrisoni falls unimportant, but later hageni better, S dors-OTan/GB, vent-ltO/ltGB. R. undulata (7mm) RB, W-motG, T- spekld ltB. Occ spectacular S falls. S dors-lt/dkRB, vent-lt/CRB, W-clr w lt B veins.
N sml smpl leaflike gls - Ameletus velox (12-14mm) Y/dkB, W-barred dkG. N lt/dk purplshB w pl areas & dk mrks on tergites, tl web, no color band. S Y/dkB, W-clr w Y&Bk mrks.

N med veined leaflk gls w filaments below, lng hairs on front of forelegs - Isonychia velma (14-18mm) Bk/dkG, W-slate, hindL-C, others C tips. N claret/RB, T-dk, L-dk w Y mks, pl dors stripe. S BkG, rearL-C, others dkB. Faster reaches of steelhead rivers.
N flouncy veined gls - Siphlonurus occidentalis (12-16mm) G/OG w brn mrks, W-smoky/dkG, L-mottled, T-G/dkG. N G/tanG. S GB w lt bnds, but var.

Crawlers (Ephemerellidae) 3 eq T. N hd & eyes wider than long, sm to med oval gls extend lat from top of segs 3 or 4-7, flutter in seq, posterolateral spines all segs. D angled hnd wng LE. Slower wtr genera less stocky, better swimmers. In prep for emergence, N migrate to slower wtr.

Fringed Crawlers (Leptophleiidae) 3 eq len T. N some genera w tusks, fine, feathery 2-pronged Bk gls segs 1-7, bdy O/dkB. D no pt or angle on hnd wng LE, plC unmarked legs. Early instars live in faster wtr, but mature ones inhabit and emerge in placid wtrs w leafy debris, N awkward swim w snake-like undulations, make practice runs. Eclose in film, float a long time while unfurling. S mate and fall immed, eve, can be heavy. Pref overcast days. E spr wtr wrms to 50ºF, fall cools low 50s.

Burrowers (Ephemeridae) Large, N frontal tusks, feathery 2-pronged gls, segs 1-7, 3 feathery T. D 2 or 3T, prom hind LE basal bump. Swim strongly up, emerge quickly on or below film, float while unfurling wings, attention grabbing takeoff, dense spinner fall, but at night. Best fish deep rising nymph 1 hr before hatch, as trout can become sated.

N crablike lgs, esp heavy serrated forefemora - Drunella - N thx often ltr than abdo. Poor swimmers, D clumsy, fluttering drift in film, color soon fades. Doddsi (12-13mm) brOG aging to RB/dkOB, W-G. N YB, dense setae bot abdo, practice runs, X below flm. Only cold, fast freestn wtrs. D. grandis (16-14mm) brGn aging to BkO, W-dkG. N BBk/mot OB. Cool slower waters. D. flavilinea (7-10mm) dkO w Y bands, W-slateG. N abdo-dkOB, thx lighter, gls B, T-C w Bk bnds. FS dkOB. Mod to fst wtrs always < 60ºF, E starting mid 50s. D. coloradensis (12mm) like flav. Only in small, fast mtn meadow strs always < 60ºF.

N last 2/3 of T w fine & coarse hairs - Ephemerella infrequens, inermis (7-9, 5.5-7mm) C or btY w O cast, W-ltG. N varB/O, gls B, T- fringed, competent swimmers (fore lgs held fwd, rear pairs trail). S ltOB. Most waters, starting tmp low 50s. F drop eggs from above, both sexes fall spent onto flm. E. tibialis (7-9mm) RB occas OB, W-G, L-C. N dkB/blueBk with pale dorsal stripe, 3 blksh T. Faster sects of med to high elev strs.
N gls segs 4-7, T cov w blk setae - Attenella margarita (7mm) O/OB, W-G. N ltAmber/dkB, segs 4,5,8 pale. X bot, slow flat wtr. S abdo-M Wt, F O, thx-BkO.

flowSpan.flowSpan: dkB, W-dkG, L-ginger. P. helena (11mm) BkB, W-dkG (Calif only).

flowRoot.flowPara: N no tusks - P. debilis (9-10mm) dkRB, W-dkSlateG, L-C. E wtr temp 50-55º F. P. gregalis (7-8mm) mahogany, W-dkSlateG, L-dkC, tolerant of wrm wtr. P. heteronea (7-9mm) dk slate/dkRB, W-dkSlateG, L-G.

Tiny Crawlers (Tricorythidae) 3T. N bdy tan/dkB w lt bands, covered with tiny setae, lg triangular 2nd gl pair, mid tl longer. D no hndW. M emerge pre-dawn below flm, quickly molt to S, F ditto, early am, mate immed. Spent M fall in place, F oviposit 1 hr later and fall. Fish spent M, laying and spent F; cast to specific fish in feeding lanes. Multibrooded.

Tricorythodes minutus M (5-6mm) dkB/Bk poss tan bands, W-ltG, L&T-WtG, T-2x bdy len. S thx-dkB/Bk, abd-dkRB/Bk, L-ltC. F (7mm) F thx-dk/GB, abd-ltG/plO, W-pl/medG. S thx-dkB/Bk, abdo-pl/dkGr, L&T-ltC, T-1x bdy len. Cool, clean, slow water with thin midsummer silted bottom, eg freestone tailouts, spring creeks.

D 3T - Ephemera simulans (18-20mm) slender, YTan/B, dk mrks on tergites, W-motB. Emerge below surface. E wtr wrms to 50ºF, hatch lasts only a few days on any piece of rvr. Cool slow to mod meandering strs with sand-and-gravel bottoms. Spent spinners may have erect wings.
D 2T - Hexagenia limbata (22-35mm) tanY/OB w prplsh mrks, W-smokyG w O cast, dk nr TE. N 2-3 yrs. Eclose on surface. Hatches last only 30-45 min. Cold, slow rivers and lakes with silted bots.
